FBIS4-14377 "drnes083dd_94010" FBIS-NES-94-083 Daily Report 24 Apr 1994 Palestinian Affairs Fatah Invites Factions to National Dialogue Fatah Invites Factions to National Dialogue TA2604150794 Jerusalem AL-NAHAR in Arabic 24 Apr 94 pp 1, 7 TA2604150794 Jerusalem AL-NAHAR Arabic BFN [By 'Abd-al-Ra'uf Arna'ut] [Excerpt] Jerusalem -- AL-NAHAR has learned that an internal dialogue among Palestinian factions that support and oppose the Palestinian-Israeli agreement is currently taking place inside and outside the occupied territories. The aim of this dialogue is to reach a draft joint agreement on unity in view of the conditions that will prevail in the occupied territories during the coming stage. Fatah has invited all Palestinian political and militant forces to a comprehensive national dialogue. The invitation, extended by Ahmad Ghunaym, head of Fatah's office in Jerusalem, during a commemorative ceremony for martyr Khalil al-Wazir, said: We invite our brothers in Hamas [Islamic Resistance Movement], the Islamic Jihad, the Popular Front for the Liberation of Palestine, the People's Party, FIDA [Palestinian Democratic Union], and all our national movements to a comprehensive dialogue in order to affirm that this homeland does not belong to one organization but to the entire people. [passage omitted]
